<p class="my-4">The <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build">build step</a> will result in an error if the output directory is missing, empty, or invalid (for example, it is not a directory). To resolve this error, you can try the following steps:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Make sure the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#output-directory">output directory</a> is specified correctly in project settings</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">If the output directory is correct, check the build command (<a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#build-command">documentation</a>) or the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#root-directory">root directory</a>)</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Try running the build command locally and make sure that the files are correctly generated in the specified output directory</li>
</ul>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="missing-build-script"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#missing-build-script">Missing build script</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>

<p class="my-4">Suppose your project contains a <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> file, no <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">api</code> directory, and no <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel.json</code> configuration. In that case, it is expected to provide a <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">build</code> <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/scripts" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">script</a> that performs a static build of your frontend and outputs it to a <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">public</code> directory at the root of your project.</p>
<p class="my-4">When properly configured, your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> file would look similar to this:</p>

directory.</p></div>
<p class="my-4">Once you have defined the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">build</code> <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/scripts" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">script</a>, this error will disappear. Furthermore, it will not be displayed if you are using <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> purely to provide dependencies for your Vercel functions located inside the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">api</code> directory.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="maximum-team-member-requests"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#maximum-team-member-requests">Maximum team member requests</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The maximum amount of open requests to join a team is 10. In order to allow for more requests, the existing requests need to be approved or declined by a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#owner-role">Team Owner</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">This ensures the list always remains manageable and protected against spam.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="inviting-users-to-team-who-requested-access"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#inviting-users-to-team-who-requested-access">Inviting users to team who requested access</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">If a user has already requested access to a team, it&#x27;s impossible to invite them. Instead, their request must be approved by a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#owner-role">Team Owner</a> for the user to gain access.</p>
<p class="my-4">This ensures no team invites are accidentally accepted.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="request-access-with-the-required-git-account"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#request-access-with-the-required-git-account">Request access with the required Git account</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">When the deployment for a commit fails with the message &quot;Team access required to deploy.&quot;, the Git account of the commit author is not connected to a Hobby team that is a member of the team.</p>
<p class="my-4">The link attached to the error allows someone to connect their Hobby team to the Git account of the commit author. If the Hobby team is connected to a different Git account, it will fail stating that a different Git account must be used to request access to the team.</p>
<p class="my-4">Once the Git account is connected to the Hobby team on Vercel, it is possible to request access to the team. A <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#owner-role">Team Owner</a> can then approve or decline this access request. If the request was approved, the failed commit would be retried, and the following commits would not fail due to missing team access.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="blocked-scopes"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#blocked-scopes">Blocked scopes</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">A deployment, project, user, or team on Vercel can be blocked if it violates our <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/limits/fair-use-guidelines">fair use guidelines</a> or <a href="/legal/terms" data-zone="6a379c" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Terms of Service</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">Blocked deployments and projects will result in your website returning a 451 error. Blocked users and teams cannot create new deployments, and blocked users cannot be invited to a team. Please reach out to <a href="mailto:registration@vercel.com" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">registration@vercel.com</a> if you need help.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="unused-build-and-development-settings"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#unused-build-and-development-settings">Unused build and development settings</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">A <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/projects/overview">Project</a> has several settings that can be found in the dashboard. One of those sections, <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Build &amp; Development Settings</span>, is used to change the way a Project is built.</p>
<p class="my-4">However, the <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Build &amp; Development Settings</span> are only applied to <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/kb/guide/upgrade-to-zero-configuration">zero-configuration</a> deployments.</p>
<p class="my-4">If a deployment defines the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#builds"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">builds</code></a> configuration property, the <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Build &amp; Development Settings</span> are ignored.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="unused-vercel-function-region-setting"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#unused-vercel-function-region-setting">Unused Vercel Function region setting</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">A <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/projects/overview">project</a> has several settings that can be found in the dashboard. One of those settings, <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Vercel Function Region</span>, is used to select the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/regions">region</a> where your Vercel functions execute.</p>
<p class="my-4">If a deployment defines the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#regions"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">regions</code></a> configuration property in <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel.json</code>, the <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Vercel Function Region</span> setting is ignored.</p>
<p class="my-4">If a CLI Deployment defines the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/cli/deploy#regions"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">--regions</code></a> option, the <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Vercel Function Region</span> setting is ignored.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="invalid-route-source-pattern"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#invalid-route-source-pattern">Invalid route source pattern</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">source</code> property follows the syntax from <a href="https://github.com/pillarjs/path-to-regexp/tree/v6.1.0" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">path-to-regexp</a>, not the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">RegExp</code> syntax.</p>
<p class="my-4">For example, negative lookaheads must be wrapped in a group.</p>

<p class="my-4">The <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">source</code> property follows the syntax from <a href="https://github.com/pillarjs/path-to-regexp/tree/v6.1.0" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">path-to-regexp</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">A colon (<code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">:</code>) defines the start of a <a href="https://github.com/pillarjs/path-to-regexp/tree/v6.1.0#named-parameters" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">named segment parameter</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">A named segment parameter defined in the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">destination</code> property must also be defined in the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">source</code> property.</p>

<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="failed-to-install-builder-dependencies"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#failed-to-install-builder-dependencies">Failed to install builder dependencies</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">When running the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel build</code> or <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code> commands, <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">npm install</code> errors can be encountered if <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">npm</code> was invoked to install Builders that are defined in your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel.json</code> file.</p>
<p class="my-4"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">npm install</code> may fail if:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/get-npm" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">npm</code></a> is not installed</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Your internet connection is unavailable</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">The Builder that is defined in your configuration is not published to the npm registry</li>
</ul>
<p class="my-4">Double-check that the name and version of the Builder you are requesting is correct.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="mixed-routing-properties"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#mixed-routing-properties">Mixed routing properties</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">If you have <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#rewrites"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">rewrites</code></a>, <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#redirects"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">redirects</code></a>, <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#headers"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">headers</code></a>, <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#cleanurls"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">cleanUrls</code></a> or <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#trailingslash"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">trailingSlash</code></a> defined in your <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration">configuration</a> file, then <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#routes"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">routes</code></a> cannot be defined.</p>
<p class="my-4">This is a necessary limitation because <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">routes</code> is a lower-level primitive that contains all of the other types. Therefore, it cannot be merged safely with the new properties.</p>
<p class="my-4">See the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration/vercel-json#upgrading-legacy-routes">Upgrading Routes</a> section for examples of <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">routes</code> compared to the new properties.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="conflicting-configuration-files"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#conflicting-configuration-files">Conflicting configuration files</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">For backward compatibility purposes, there are two naming conventions for configuration files used by Vercel CLI (for example <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel.json</code> and <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">now.json</code>). Both naming conventions are supported, however only <em>one</em> may be defined at a time. Vercel CLI will output an error message if both naming conventions are used at the same time.</p>
<p class="my-4">These conflicting configuration errors occur if:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Both <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel.json</code> and <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">now.json</code> exist in your project.<br/><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Solution:</span> Delete the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">now.json</code> file</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Both <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.vercel</code> and <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.now</code> directories exist in your project.<br/><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Solution:</span> Delete the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.now</code> directory</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Both <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.vercelignore</code> and <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.nowignore</code> files exist in your project.<br/><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Solution:</span> Delete the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.nowignore</code> file</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Environment Variables that begin with <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">VERCEL_</code> have a conflicting Environment Variable that begins with <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">NOW_</code>.<br/><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Solution:</span> Only define the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">VERCEL_</code> prefixed Environment Variable</li>
</ul>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="conflicting-functions-and-builds-configuration"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#conflicting-functions-and-builds-configuration">Conflicting functions and builds configuration</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">There are two ways to configure Vercel functions in your project: <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#functions">functions</a> <em>or</em> <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#builds"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">builds</code></a>. However, only one of them may be used at a time - they cannot be used in conjunction.</p>
<p class="my-4">For most cases, it is recommended to use the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">functions</code> property because it supports more features, such as:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Allows configuration of the amount of memory that the Vercel Function is provided with</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">More reliable because it requires a specific npm package version for the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">runtime</code> property</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Supports &quot;clean URLs&quot; by default, which means that the Vercel functions are automatically accessible without their file extension in the URL</li>
</ul>
<p class="my-4">However, the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#builds"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">builds</code></a> property will remain supported for backward compatibility purposes.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="unsupported-functions-configuration-with-nextjs"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#unsupported-functions-configuration-with-nextjs">Unsupported functions configuration with Nextjs</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">When using Next.js, only <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">memory</code> and <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">maxDuration</code> can be configured within the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#functions">functions</a> property. Next.js automatically handles the other configuration values for you.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="deploying-vercel-functions-to-multiple-regions"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#deploying-vercel-functions-to-multiple-regions">Deploying Vercel functions to multiple regions</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">It&#x27;s possible to deploy Vercel functions to multiple regions. This functionality is only available to <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/plans/enterprise">Enterprise teams</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">On the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/plans/pro-plan">Pro plan</a>, the limitation has existed since the <a href="/blog/simpler-pricing" data-zone="6a379c" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">launch</a> of the current pricing model but was applied on <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">July 10, 2020</span>. For Projects created on or after the date, it&#x27;s no longer possible to deploy to multiple regions.</p>
<p class="my-4">To select the region closest to you, read our <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/functions/configuring-functions/region">guide</a> on choosing deployment regions for Vercel functions.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="unmatched-function-pattern"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#unmatched-function-pattern">Unmatched function pattern</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/project-configuration#functions">functions</a> property uses a glob pattern for each key. This pattern must match Vercel Function source files within the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">api</code> directory.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you are using Next.js, Vercel functions source files can be created in the following:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">pages/api</code> directory</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">src/pages/api</code> directory</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">pages</code> directory when the module exports <a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/data-fetching/get-server-side-props" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">getServerSideProps</a></li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">src/pages</code> directory when the module exports <a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/data-fetching/get-server-side-props" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">getServerSideProps</a></li>
</ul>
<p class="my-4">Additionally, if you&#x27;d like to use a Vercel Function that isn&#x27;t written with Node.js, and in combination with Next.js, you can place it in the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">api</code> directory (provided by the platform), since <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">pages/api</code> (provided by Next.js) only supports JavaScript.</p>
<p class="my-4"><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Not Allowed</span></p>

<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="cannot-load-project-settings"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#cannot-load-project-settings">Cannot load project settings</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">If the Project configuration in <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.vercel</code> belongs to a team you are not a member of, attempting to deploy the project will result in an error.</p>
<p class="my-4">This can occur if you clone a Git repository that includes the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.vercel</code> directory, or you are logged in to the wrong Vercel account.
Additionally, authentication issues can occur if you don&#x27;t comply with the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/two-factor-enforcement">two-factor enforcement</a> policy of your team.</p>
<p class="my-4">To fix, remove the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.vercel</code> directory and redeploy to link the project again by running these commands.</p>
<p class="my-4">On macOS and Linux:</p>

<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="project-name-validation"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#project-name-validation">Project name validation</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">Project names can only consist of up to one hundred alphanumeric lowercase characters. Hyphens can be used in between words in the name, but never at the start or end.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="repository-connection-limitation"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#repository-connection-limitation">Repository connection limitation</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The amount of Vercel Projects that can be connected with the same Git repository is <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/limits#general-limits">limited depending on your plan</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you have reached the limitation and would like to connect a new project to the repository, you will need to disconnect an existing project from the same Git repository.</p>
<p class="my-4">To increase this limit, please <a href="/contact/sales" data-zone="6a379c" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">contact our Sales Team</a>.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="domain-verification-through-cli"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#domain-verification-through-cli">Domain verification through CLI</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">To verify your domain, point the domain to Vercel by configuring our nameservers or a DNS Record. You can learn more about what to do for your Domain by running <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel domains inspect &lt;domain&gt;</code>, where <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">&lt;domain&gt;</code> is the domain you&#x27;re interested in.</p>
<p class="my-4">Alternatively, if you already added the domain to a project, read <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/projects/custom-domains#step-4:-configuring-the-domain">the configuring a domain section</a> of the custom domain documentation.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="leaving-the-team"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#leaving-the-team">Leaving the team</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">You cannot leave a team if you are the last remaining <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#owner-role">Owner</a> or the last confirmed <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#member-role">Member</a>. In order to leave the Team, first designate a different confirmed <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#member-role">Member</a> to be an <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#owner-role">Team Owner</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you are the only remaining <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#member-role">Member</a>, you should instead delete the Team.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="git-default-ignore-list"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#git-default-ignore-list">Git Default ignore list</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">Deployments created using Vercel CLI will automatically <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/build-features#ignored-files-and-folders">ignore several files</a> for security and performance reasons.</p>
<p class="my-4">However, these files are <em>not</em> ignored for deployments created using <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/git">Git</a> and a warning is printed instead. This is because <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">.gitignore</code> determines which files should be ignored.</p>
<p class="my-4">If the file was intentionally committed to Git, you can ignore the warning.</p>
<p class="my-4">If the file was accidentally committed to Git, you can remove it using the following commands:</p>
