<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="github-app-installation-not-found"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#github-app-installation-not-found">GitHub app installation not found</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">In some cases, signing up with GitHub fails due to GitHub&#x27;s database inconsistencies.</p>
<p class="my-4">When you connected your Hobby team with your GitHub account, the <a href="https://github.com/apps/vercel" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Vercel GitHub App</a> was installed on your GitHub account and then GitHub notified Vercel that the app was successfully installed.</p>
<p class="my-4">However, Vercel was unable to retrieve the app installation from GitHub, which made it appear as if the <a href="https://github.com/apps/vercel" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Vercel GitHub App</a> was never installed.</p>
<p class="my-4">In order to solve this issue, wait a couple of minutes and try connecting to GitHub again. If you are still unable to connect, please contact <a href="https://support.github.com/contact" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">GitHub Support</a> to determine why the <a href="https://github.com/apps/vercel" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Vercel GitHub App</a> was not able to be installed.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="preview-branch-used-as-production-branch"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#preview-branch-used-as-production-branch">Preview branch used as production branch</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">If you have configured a custom Git branch for a domain or an environment variable, it is considered a preview domain and a preview environment variable. Because of this, the Git branch configured for it is considered a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/git#preview-branches">preview branch</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">When configuring the production branch in the project settings, it is not possible to use a preview branch.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you still want to use this particular Git branch as a production branch, please follow these steps:</p>
<ol class="my-3 list-decimal pl-4">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Assign your affected domains to the production environment (clear out the Git branch you&#x27;ve defined for them)</li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Assign your affected environment variables to the production environment (clear out the Git branch you&#x27;ve defined for them)</li>
</ol>
<p class="my-4">Afterwards, you can use the Git branch you originally wanted to use as a production branch.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="lost-git-repository-access"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#lost-git-repository-access">Lost Git repository access</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">In order for Vercel to be able to deploy commits to your Git repository, a Project on Vercel has to be connected to it.</p>
<p class="my-4">This connection is interrupted if the Git repository is deleted, archived, or if the Vercel App was uninstalled from the corresponding Git account or Git organization. Make sure none of these things apply.</p>
<p class="my-4">Additionally, when using GitHub, the connection is also interrupted if you or a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/rbac/access-roles#member-role">Team Member</a> modifies the access permissions of the Vercel GitHub App installed on the respective personal GitHub account or GitHub organization.</p>
<p class="my-4">To verify the access permissions of the Vercel GitHub App installed on your personal GitHub account, navigate to the <a href="https://github.com/settings/installations" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend"><span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Applications</span> page</a> and select <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Vercel</span> under <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Installed GitHub Apps</span>. You will see a list of Git repositories that the GitHub App has access to. Make sure that the Git repository you&#x27;re looking to connect to a Vercel Project is listed there.</p>
<p class="my-4">To verify the access permissions of the Vercel GitHub App installed on your GitHub organization, select <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Vercel</span> under <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Installed GitHub Apps</span> in the organization settings. You will see a list of Git repositories that the GitHub App has access to. Make sure that the Git repository you&#x27;re looking to connect to a Vercel Project is listed there.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="production-deployment-cannot-be-redeployed"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#production-deployment-cannot-be-redeployed">Production deployment cannot be redeployed</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">You cannot redeploy a production deployment if a more recent one exists.</p>
<p class="my-4">The reason is that redeploying an old production deployment would result in overwriting the most recent source code you have deployed to production.</p>
<p class="my-4">To force an explicit overwrite of the current production deployment, select <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Promote</span> instead.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="ssl-certificate-deletion-denied"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#ssl-certificate-deletion-denied">SSL certificate deletion denied</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">Certain SSL Certificates associated with your Hobby team or team (i.e. Wildcard SSL Certificates for your Vercel Project&#x27;s staging domains) are automatically generated by the Vercel platform.</p>
<p class="my-4">Because these SSL Certificates are managed by the Vercel platform, they cannot be manually deleted on the Vercel Dashboard â€“ nor through Vercel CLI.</p>
<p class="my-4">Custom SSL Certificates may be uploaded to teams on the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/plans/enterprise">Enteprise plan</a>, which are allowed to be manually deleted.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="production-branch-used-as-preview-branch"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#production-branch-used-as-preview-branch">Production branch used as preview branch</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The Git branch that is configured using the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/git#production-branch">production branch</a> field in the project settings, is considered the branch that contains the code served to your visitors.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you&#x27;d like to assign a domain or environment variable to that particular Git branch, there&#x27;s no need to manually fill it in.</p>
<p class="my-4">By default, if no custom Git branch is defined for them, domains are already assigned to the production branch. The same is true for environment variables: If no custom Git branch is defined for them and <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Production</span> is selected as an environment, they&#x27;re already assigned to the production branch.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you still want to enter a specific Git branch for a domain or an environment variable, it has to be a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/git#preview-branches">preview branch</a>.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="command-not-found-in-vercel-dev"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#command-not-found-in-vercel-dev">Command not found in vercel dev</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">The <em>&quot;Command not found&quot;</em> error message happens when a sub-process that <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code> is attempting to create is not installed on your local machine. You need to install the particular program onto your operating system before <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code> will work correctly.</p>
<p class="my-4">For example, you may see the error <em>&quot;Command not found: go&quot;</em> if you are writing a Vercel Function in Go, but do not have the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">go</code> binary installed. In this case you need to <a href="https://golang.org/doc/install" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">install <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">go</code></a> first, and then try invoking your Vercel Function again.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="recursive-invocation-of-commands"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#recursive-invocation-of-commands">Recursive invocation of commands</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h3 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-24" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="why-this-error-occurred"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#why-this-error-occurred">Why this error occurred</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h3></div>
<p class="my-4">You have configured one of the following for your Project:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">The <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#build-command">Build Command</a> defined in the Project Settings invokes <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel build</code></li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">The <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#development-command">Development Command</a> defined in the Project Settings invokes <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code></li>
</ul>
<p class="my-4">Because the Build Command is invoked by <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel build</code> when deploying, it cannot invoke <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel build</code> itself, as that would cause an infinite recursion.</p>
<p class="my-4">The same applies to the Development Command: When developing locally, <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code> invokes the Development Command, so it cannot invoke <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code> itself.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h3 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-24" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="possible-ways-to-fix-it"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#possible-ways-to-fix-it">Possible ways to fix it</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h3></div>
<p class="my-4">Adjust the Build and Development Commands defined for your Project to not invoke <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel build</code> or <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">vercel dev</code>.</p>
<p class="my-4">Instead, they should invoke the Build Command provided by your framework.</p>
<p class="my-4">If you are unsure about which value to provide, disable the <span class="strong-module__WGWgwq__docsString">Override</span> option in order to default to the preferred settings for the <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#framework-preset">Framework Preset</a> you have selected.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="pnpm-engine-unsupported"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#pnpm-engine-unsupported">Pnpm engine unsupported</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">ERR_PNPM_UNSUPPORTED_ENGINE</code> occurs when <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json#engines.pnpm</code> does not match the currently running version of <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">pnpm</code>.</p>
<p class="my-4">To fix, do one of the following:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0"><a href="https://vercel.com/docs/deployments/configure-a-build#corepack" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Set the env var <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_COREPACK</code> to 1</a>, and make sure the <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">packageManager</code> value is set correctly in your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code></li>
</ul>

<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Remove the <a href="https://pnpm.io/package_json#engines" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">engines.pnpm</code></a> value from your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code></li>
</ul>
<div class="py-2 px-3 flex flex-col grow items-start justify-between sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-3 gap-2 min-h-10 rounded-md text-sm leading-normal break-words box-border [&amp;_svg]:!h-[1lh] text-left v3-colors" data-geist-note="" data-version="v1"><div class="m-0 flex items-start" style="gap:12px"><span class="flex h-4"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" height="16" width="16" data-slot="geist-icon" style="color:currentColor"><path fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8 14.5a6.5 6.5 0 1 0 0-13 6.5 6.5 0 0 0 0 13M8 16A8 8 0 1 0 8 0a8 8 0 0 0 0 16M6.25 7h1.5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v4.25h-1.5V8.5h-1zM8 6a1 1 0 1 0 0-2 1 1 0 0 0 0 2" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span><span><p class="my-4">You cannot use <a href="https://pnpm.io/npmrc#engine-strict" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">engine-strict</code></a> to solve
this error. <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">engine-strict</code> only handles dependencies.</p></span></div></div>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="yarn-dynamic-require-of-util-is-not-supported"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#yarn-dynamic-require-of-util-is-not-supported">Yarn dynamic require of &quot;util&quot; is not supported</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">This error occurs when projects use yarn, corepack, and have a <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> with a <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">type</code> field set to <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">module</code>. This is a known <a href="https://github.com/yarnpkg/berry/issues/5831" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">yarn issue</a>.</p>
<p class="my-4">To prevent this error, consider the following options:</p>
<ul class="my-3 list-disc pl-4 [&amp;&gt;li::marker]:text-gray-600">
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Remove <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">&quot;type&quot;: &quot;module&quot;</code> from the project&#x27;s <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code></li>
<li class="mb-[10px] pl-2 leading-(--line-height-primary) [&amp;&gt;svg]:inline-flex last:mb-0">Install yarn into the project instead of using corepack with <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">yarn set version [desired-version] --yarn-path</code></li>
</ul>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="invalid-edge-config-connection-string"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#invalid-edge-config-connection-string">Invalid Edge Config connection string</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">This error occurs when attempting to create a deployment where at least one of its environment variables contains an outdated Edge Config connection string. A connection string can be outdated if either the Edge Config itself was deleted or if the token used in the connection string is invalid or has been deleted.</p>
<p class="my-4">To resolve this error, delete or update the environment variable that contains the connection string. In most cases, the environment variable is named <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">EDGE_CONFIG</code>.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="globally-installed-@vercel/speed-insights-or-@vercel/analytics-packages"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#globally-installed-@vercel/speed-insights-or-@vercel/analytics-packages">Globally installed <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">@vercel/speed-insights</code> or <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">@vercel/analytics</code> packages</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4">You must reference <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">@vercel/speed-insights</code> or <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">@vercel/analytics</code> packages in your application&#x27;s <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> file. This error occurs when you deploy your application with these packages globally available, but not referenced in your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> file, like in a monorepo.</p>
<p class="my-4">To fix this error, add the packages to your <code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">package.json</code> file as a dependency.</p>
<div class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__container"><h2 class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__header text-heading-20 sm:text-heading-32" data-components-heading="true"><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__target" id="oversized-incremental-static-regeneration-page"></span><a class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__title [&amp;&gt;p]:m-0" href="#oversized-incremental-static-regeneration-page">Oversized Incremental Static Regeneration page</a><span class="linked-heading-module__rvMliW__permalink"><svg class="text-[0.6em]" data-testid="geist-icon" height="16" stroke-linejoin="round" style="color:currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg></span></h2></div>
<p class="my-4"><a href="https://vercel.com/docs/incremental-static-regeneration" rel="noopener" target="_blank" data-zone="null" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend">Incremental Static Regeneration</a> (ISR) responses that are greater than 20 MB result in pages not rendering in production with a <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/errors/FALLBACK_BODY_TOO_LARGE"><code class="code-module__V4tPXG__code code-module__V4tPXG__inlineCode">FALLBACK_BODY_TOO_LARGE</code></a> error. This affects all Next.js build time pre-rendering, and other frameworks that use <a data-zone="same" class="link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__blend" href="/docs/build-output-api/v3/primitives#prerender-functions">Prerender Functions</a>.</p></div></div><hr class="border-top-[1px] my-12 border-0 border-solid border-[var(--accents-2)] sm:my-9"/><div
